This paper is about a new framework for Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) that addresses the issue of gradient vanishing and does not require the 1-Lipschitz constraint on the discriminator. Therefore, it is likely to be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and systems and control (cs.SD).
